{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb500db25-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s256"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"256"},"text":"§ 256.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Sense of Congress regarding construction of fencing near San Diego, California","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"It is the sense of the Congress that completing the 14-mile border fence project required to be carried out under section 102(b) of the Illegal Immigration Reform and Immigrant Responsibility Act of 1996 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t8/s1103"},"text":"8 U.S.C. 1103","children":[],"tail":" note) should be a priority for the Secretary."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb500db26-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296/tIV/s446"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–296, title IV, § 446","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2195"},"text":"116 Stat. 2195","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb500db27-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb500db28-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb500db29-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 102(b) of the Illegal Immigration Reform and Immigrant Responsibility Act o